MogileFS is a open source distribued filesystem. www.Danga.com/MogileFS/

Maintainers : AHSEIN Khalid < k@capoune.net >
License : BSD License

Description
This extension allows you to communicate with the MogileFS tracker.
Mogilefs.php is a Class to use mogilefs storage functions easily.

INSTALL MOGILEFS

$ phpize
$ ./configure --with-mogilefs
# make install

FUNCTIONS
    * bool MogileFsClient::connect (string host, int port, string domain)
    * bool MogileFsClient::close
    * bool MogileFsClient::put (file, string key, string class)
    * array MogileFsClient::getPaths (string key)
    * bool MogileFsClient::delete (string key)
    * bool MogileFsClient::rename (string from_key, string to_key)
    * bool MogileFsClient::listKeys (string prefix, string after, integer limit)
    * bool MogileFsClient::listFids (integer from, integer to)
    * array MogileFsClient::getDomains
    * array MogileFsClient::getHosts
    * array MogileFsClient::getDevices
    * bool MogileFsClient::sleep (integer duration)
    * array MogileFsClient::stats (ingeter all)
    * bool MogileFsClient::replicate
    * array MogileFsClient::createDevice (string devid, string status)
    * array MogileFsClient::createDomain (string domain)
    * array MogileFsClient::deleteDomain (string domain)
    * array MogileFsClient::createClass (string domain, string class, string mindevcount)
    * array MogileFsClient::updateClass (string domain, string class, string mindevcount)
    * array MogileFsClient::createHost (string hostname)
    * array MogileFsClient::updateHost (string hostname, string ip, string port, string state[dead, alive]) default alive
    * bool MogileFsClient::deleteHost (string hostname)
    * bool MogileFsClient::setWeight (string hostname, string device, string weight)
    * bool MogileFsClient::setState (string hostname, string device, string state[dead, alive] ) default alive
    * bool MogileFsClient::checker (string on/off, string level)

EXAMPLE

<?php
/****
  Example using mogilefs object API
****/
$mg = new MogileFsClient();
$mg->connect('192.168.101.1', 6001, 'myDomain');
$mg->put('/example/file.jpg', 'my_key', 'my_class');
$paths = $mg->getPaths('my_key');
$mg->close();


/****
  Example using mogilefs procedural API
****/
$mg_object = mogilefs_connect('192.168.101.1', 6001, 'myDomain');
mogilefs_put($mg_object, '/example/file.jpg', 'my_key', 'my_class');
$paths = mogilefs_get_paths($mg_object, 'my_key');
mogilefs_close($mg_object);
?>
